  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "心理逆反 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-reactance",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / autonomy / pressure / pushback</p>\n    <h1>心理逆反</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Reactance</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">當人感覺自己的選擇自由被硬推、被命令或被操控時，常會出現反作用力，讓原本可能接受的建議也變得想抗拒。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『內容是對的』和『講法讓人想反抗』拆開，因為很多推動失敗不是立場錯，而是侵犯感先被點燃。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>動機心理 / 自主防衛</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>People push back when they feel their freedom is threatened</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>自由感、命令強度、選擇空間、反作用力</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能在說服、產品限制與流程推動裡更敏感地處理自主感</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>被逼</span>\n      <span>反彈</span>\n      <span>自主</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>人不只在回應建議內容，也在回應自己是否被當成有選擇的人</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">心理逆反讓我們看到：壓力過大時，阻力不一定來自觀點本身，而來自被控制的感受。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>有些情境確實需要明確要求，但命令感一旦過強，就可能讓原本可合作的人轉而把拒絕本身當成恢復自主的方式。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先保留選擇感</strong>\n        <p>就算方向已定，也要讓對方知道自己還有理解、參與或調整空間。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再降低被操控感</strong>\n        <p>硬壓式語言常比內容本身更早引發抵抗。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後把理由說完整</strong>\n        <p>當限制無法避免時，透明理由能降低『只是被控制』的感受。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一個本來合理、卻越推越被反著做的要求開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">心理逆反在管理、教學、家長式產品設計與規則推動中特別常見。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>你越強調某流程『一定要這樣做』，團隊越開始挑戰它的合理性，甚至連原本同意的人也開始防衛。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>人反抗的常不是規則內容本身，而是那種『我被剝奪選擇』的感覺。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">外界施加強制感</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">自主感被威脅</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">個體以抗拒恢復主體性</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>心理逆反提醒你：推動改變時，自主感本身也是設計變數。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看反彈來源的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">當你越說越沒用，不妨先看是不是內容還沒被評估，形式就已經先惹怒人。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>語氣強度</strong>\n        <p>這是在說明必要性，還是在宣布不容討論？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>選項空間</strong>\n        <p>對方是否仍保有某種參與、選擇或例外處理的空間？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>身份敏感度</strong>\n        <p>越涉及專業、自我控制感或成熟自主，逆反越容易被點亮。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>理由透明度</strong>\n        <p>規則若只剩權威，沒有脈絡，反彈通常更強。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>做法</th>\n            <th>短期感受</th>\n            <th>常見回應</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>硬性命令</td>\n            <td>被控制</td>\n            <td>表面服從、私下抵抗或消極執行</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>說明理由但保留選擇</td>\n            <td>被尊重</td>\n            <td>較容易合作或至少可談判</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>過度 nudging</td>\n            <td>被操控</td>\n            <td>一旦被看穿反而更不信任</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼自由感被碰到時，反作用力這麼快</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為自主不只是偏好，它和尊嚴、身份與能力感都綁在一起。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>控制感是核心資源</strong>\n        <p>一旦被抽走，人會自然想把它搶回來。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>命令會觸發防衛</strong>\n        <p>就算內容合理，只要形式像被壓制，抗拒就可能先上來。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>越像自己領域越敏感</strong>\n        <p>人對自己專業或生活邊界內的強制，通常更容易產生逆反。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">心理逆反不是說不能設規則，而是說規則推動要理解自主感是現實力量。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把自主感帶回產品與管理設計</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對產品與工程團隊來說，很多規範被鑽洞、很多 UI 被嫌煩，不全是因為內容差，也可能是逆反被點起來。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>安全政策</strong>\n        <p>若只用『一定要』推行，工程師可能轉向尋找繞路而不是理解風險。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>產品限制</strong>\n        <p>強制導向某路徑若缺少說明與退出感，使用者更容易產生敵意。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>帶人與 mentoring</strong>\n        <p>直接接管別人的做法，常比陪他一起建立判斷更容易引發防衛。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>當你想推動一件好事時，請同時設計內容正確性與自主感維持方式。</li>\n      <li>如果阻力異常強，別只怪對方固執，也要看自己是不是把『被尊重』拿掉了。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">心理逆反不是說規則都不該存在，而是說規則若忽略自主感，執行成本會飆高。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只要給選擇就能解決一切</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>有時限制確實必要，但你仍要處理它帶來的侵犯感。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>反彈代表內容一定錯</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不一定，有時是形式先把人推走。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>這只在青少年或消費者身上</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>專業團隊對被控制感同樣敏感。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>對方是在反對內容，還是在反對被這樣對待</h2>\n      </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>如果我用更尊重自主的方式表述，對方還會同樣反對嗎</strong>\n        <p>這能幫你分辨內容阻力和形式阻力。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>我現在拿掉了對方哪些可感知的選擇空間</strong>\n        <p>那往往就是逆反的燃點。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 self-determination theory、nudging 與 persuasion。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 reactance 為主，再把概念帶回規範推動、產品限制與說服場景。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Reactance 條目整理了自由受威脅時，人如何產生反作用力。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reactance_(psychology)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Reactance</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>動機背景</strong>\n        <p>Self-determination theory 可作為對照，理解自主感為何如此重要。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Self-determination_theory\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Self-Determination Theory</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>相鄰場景</strong>\n        <p>Nudge theory 條目有助於理解影響設計何時會被讀成協助、何時會被讀成操控。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nudge_theory\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Nudge Theory</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以回頭看一個你推很久都推不動的規範，試著分辨大家在反的是內容還是形式。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
